<task id="009" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-09 Split Execution Context: `ToolExecutionContext` (playbook) + `ChatInvocationContext` (chat) (Pillar 2)</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>006</dependencies>
    <blocks>010</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, refactoring, ai</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies `.cs` files in `Services/Ai/` ; refactors core handler context type; downstream blocker for adapter; tags `bff-api` + `ai`.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Different files from 007 (DTO) and 008 (DTO); can run alongside.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Split the existing handler execution context into two derived types sharing a common
    base: `ToolExecutionContext` keeps playbook-node semantics (existing nodeContext,
    playbookId, action, etc.); new `ChatInvocationContext` adds chat-session semantics
    (chatSessionId, conversationHistory ref, LLM-parameter-passing). Both inherit a shared
    base `ToolInvocationContextBase` so handlers receive the appropriate type.

    Critical-path context: this split is what lets one handler (e.g.,
    `EntityExtractorHandler` after task H-G2 ships) be invoked from both a playbook node
    AND a chat tool — and access the context appropriate to the invocation. The adapter
    in task 010 wraps an `IToolHandler` and feeds it the `ChatInvocationContext`; the
    existing playbook pipeline continues to feed `ToolExecutionContext`.

    Backward-compat is binding: existing handlers (`GenericAnalysisHandler`,
    `DocumentClassifierHandler`, `SummaryHandler`, `SemanticSearchToolHandler`) MUST
    continue to compile + work unchanged. If they reference `ToolExecutionContext`
    explicitly, the rename of the existing type preserves them; the new
    `ChatInvocationContext` is additive.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with deep understanding of `IAnalysisToolHandler` /
    `ToolExecutionContext` and the playbook-node execution model.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `ToolInvocationContextBase` exists; `ToolExecutionContext` derives (playbook-node
    semantics preserved); `ChatInvocationContext` is new (chat-session semantics).
    All existing handlers + playbook pipeline + tests pass unchanged. Build green;
    publish-size delta reported.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
